253
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.198
Oh.

254
00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:22.033
School's alive.

255
00:12:22.075 --> 00:12:24.118
<i>♪♪</i>

256
00:12:24.160 --> 00:12:26.162
Um...

257
00:12:26.204 --> 00:12:28.831
Can you help me find my...

258
00:12:30.458 --> 00:12:33.086
[dramatic music]

259
00:12:33.127 --> 00:12:38.341
<i>♪♪</i>

260
00:12:55.692 --> 00:12:57.818
Wow, this is for me?

261
00:12:57.860 --> 00:12:59.487
I know, right?

262
00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:02.198
This school totally
customizes our rooms for us.

263
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:03.408
It's so cozy.

264
00:13:03.450 --> 00:13:06.035
I'm Frankie, pronouns they/them.

265
00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:07.370
I'm only 15 days old.

266
00:13:07.412 --> 00:13:09.706
Hi, Clawdeen, she/her.
Nice to meet ya.

267
00:13:09.748 --> 00:13:11.207
My full name is Frankie Stein.

268
00:13:11.249 --> 00:13:12.751
I was just created
by my parents,

269
00:13:12.791 --> 00:13:14.628
but not in the way
that others are created

270
00:13:14.669 --> 00:13:16.379
by their parents,
like werewolves.

271
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:18.172
I was actually made
in the lab using some

272
00:13:18.214 --> 00:13:20.091
of the world's most impressive
historical figures as parts.

273
00:13:20.841 --> 00:13:22.885
Did you know that the word
werewolf comes

274
00:13:22.927 --> 00:13:24.345
from the old English "werwulf,"

275
00:13:24.387 --> 00:13:25.888
although many believe
the original origin

276
00:13:25.930 --> 00:13:27.848
is the Norse "varúlfur,"
which is hard to say.

277
00:13:27.890 --> 00:13:29.267
It means "one in wolf's skin."

278
00:13:29.309 --> 00:13:31.645
I did not know any of that.
[laughs]

279
00:13:31.686 --> 00:13:33.688
I didn't know
I knew any of that.

280
00:13:33.730 --> 00:13:35.856
I've got a bunch of famous
brain parts in my head,

281
00:13:35.898 --> 00:13:39.736
like Einstein, Marie Curie,
Plato, some lady named Liz

282
00:13:39.778 --> 00:13:41.112
who apparently
invented the internet

283
00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:42.530
but didn't get any credit.

284
00:13:42.572 --> 00:13:45.366
I guess I've got
all the knowledge, too.

285
00:13:45.408 --> 00:13:49.954
Oh, sorry, loose joints.

286
00:13:49.996 --> 00:13:52.915
So is it just us creeps in here?

287
00:13:52.957 --> 00:13:55.460
I don't think so 'cause there's

288
00:13:55.502 --> 00:13:57.295
there's also that.

289
00:13:57.337 --> 00:14:01.132
[dramatic organ music]

290
00:14:01.174 --> 00:14:02.841
How can you tell
if they're home?

291
00:14:02.883 --> 00:14:04.594
Maybe we knock.

292
00:14:04.636 --> 00:14:06.971
Never knock on a closed coffin.

293
00:14:07.013 --> 00:14:09.599
Hi, I'm Clawdeen,
and this is Frankie.

294
00:14:09.641 --> 00:14:11.850
- And we are your new...
- Roommates.

295
00:14:11.892 --> 00:14:13.687
Welcome, I'm Draculaura.

296
00:14:13.728 --> 00:14:15.021
Is this your first time
sharing a dorm room?

297
00:14:15.062 --> 00:14:16.564
- Yeah.
- Yes, it is.

298
00:14:16.606 --> 00:14:19.025
Okay, great.
Let's talk ground rules.

299
00:14:19.066 --> 00:14:20.777
And don't take this
the wrong way.

300
00:14:20.819 --> 00:14:23.946
I'm just a private person.
This side of the room is mine.

301
00:14:23.988 --> 00:14:26.240
That side is yours.
Got it?

302
00:14:26.282 --> 00:14:28.284
- Yeah.
- Wow.

303
00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:30.745
Do you think of this as,
like, a house or a bed?

304
00:14:30.787 --> 00:14:33.498
Okay, okay, out.
My side. Remember?

305
00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:35.333
You know, the type of monster

306
00:14:35.375 --> 00:14:37.168
who loves to be surrounded
with others

307
00:14:37.210 --> 00:14:39.045
