387
00:17:59.286 --> 00:18:01.330
- Oh. Uh...
- Hey.

388
00:18:01.372 --> 00:18:03.666
Standing up to Cleo like that?

389
00:18:03.708 --> 00:18:04.834
Courageous move.

390
00:18:04.876 --> 00:18:06.836
- I'm Deuce.
- [snake rattles]

391
00:18:06.878 --> 00:18:08.421
You're a Gorgon.

392
00:18:08.462 --> 00:18:11.257
Oh, yeah, but not necessarily
that kind of Gorgon.

393
00:18:11.298 --> 00:18:13.175
I've got a strict no snake bites

394
00:18:13.217 --> 00:18:15.219
or turning anyone
to stone policy.

395
00:18:15.261 --> 00:18:17.346
Thus, the slightly
pretentious glasses.

396
00:18:17.388 --> 00:18:19.223
It's a good look.
I'm Clawdeen.

397
00:18:19.265 --> 00:18:21.350
I'm Frankie.
I'm 16 days old.

398
00:18:21.392 --> 00:18:22.936
Nice to meet you both.

399
00:18:22.977 --> 00:18:26.313
And don't listen to Cleo.
She's got mummy issues.

400
00:18:26.355 --> 00:18:28.190
She was wrapped in linen
for a thousand years.

401
00:18:28.232 --> 00:18:29.734
Not great for the heart.

402
00:18:29.776 --> 00:18:31.444
I should know.
I dated her.

403
00:18:31.485 --> 00:18:34.196
My heart belonged
to a dead fisherman named Earl.

404
00:18:34.238 --> 00:18:36.032
You dated her?

405
00:18:36.074 --> 00:18:38.659
Uh, yeah,
but I'm trying not to be

406
00:18:38.701 --> 00:18:41.996
who I was anymore,
if that makes any sense.

407
00:18:42.038 --> 00:18:44.248
Weirdly, it does.

408
00:18:44.290 --> 00:18:46.918
Anyways, I'll see you around.

409
00:18:48.252 --> 00:18:51.798
[Bloodgood] <i>Clawdeen Wolf, please
