So early in the week.

416
00:19:20.451 --> 00:19:23.955
100% pure ogre bone, very rare.

417
00:19:23.997 --> 00:19:26.040
It was given to me
by Joan of Arc after her death,

418
00:19:26.082 --> 00:19:28.793
of course,
which was on a Monday.

419
00:19:28.835 --> 00:19:30.503
[laughs]

420
00:19:30.544 --> 00:19:34.214
Is there a reason I'm here,
Headmistress Bloodgood?

421
00:19:34.256 --> 00:19:35.842
Yes, right.

422
00:19:35.883 --> 00:19:38.218
I just wanted
to welcome you personally.

423
00:19:38.260 --> 00:19:40.346
Your mother, well,

424
00:19:40.387 --> 00:19:42.682
a true monster heart
if there ever was one.

425
00:19:42.723 --> 00:19:44.183
Out of respect for her,

426
00:19:44.224 --> 00:19:46.853
I would like to bestow
upon you a great honor.

427
00:19:46.894 --> 00:19:49.313
Founder's Day is in a few weeks,

428
00:19:49.355 --> 00:19:50.898
the day we celebrate
the opening of the school

429
00:19:50.940 --> 00:19:52.441
when we liberated ourselves

430
00:19:52.483 --> 00:19:54.443
from the tyranny
of human society.

431
00:19:54.485 --> 00:19:57.321
There's an annual dinner,
very exclusive,

432
00:19:57.363 --> 00:20:00.867
for the school's most important
and generous officers,

433
00:20:00.908 --> 00:20:04.620
and I've selected you to be
the student ambassador to it.

434
00:20:04.662 --> 00:20:06.956
Really, me?

435
00:20:06.998 --> 00:20:09.625
Yes, many of the guests
were friends with your mother.

436
00:20:09.667 --> 00:20:11.335
You'll represent
the student body,

437
00:20:11.377 --> 00:20:14.005
say a few words about yourself,
your family.

438
00:20:14.047 --> 00:20:15.548
I'd be honored.

439
00:20:15.589 --> 00:20:19.052
- Wait, uh, my family?
- Which reminds me,

440
00:20:19.093 --> 00:20:21.721
you didn't mention your father
on your application.

441
00:20:21.762 --> 00:20:23.389
- [tense music]
- [heart pounding]

442
00:20:23.430 --> 00:20:25.599
You do have a father, don't you?

443
00:20:25.641 --> 00:20:29.478
Oh, yes, his name is...

444
00:20:29.520 --> 00:20:31.313
Pierre.

445
00:20:31.355 --> 00:20:32.523
Pierre?

446
00:20:32.565 --> 00:20:35.317
That's not
a very monstrous name.

447
00:20:35.359 --> 00:20:37.904
He isn't human, is he?

448
00:20:37.945 --> 00:20:39.197
[heart pounding faster]

449
00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:42.491
[laughs]

450
00:20:42.533 --> 00:20:44.202
Humans are the enemy,
always have been.

451
00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:46.328
We can't have any
at Monster High,

452
00:20:46.370 --> 00:20:47.997
only true monster hearts.

453
00:20:48.039 --> 00:20:51.667
No, not human.
He is all werewolf.

454
00:20:51.709 --> 00:20:57.131
Pierre Wolf, he's French.

455
00:20:57.173 --> 00:21:00.176
[Bloodgood]
Hmm, French werewolf,

456
00:21:00.218 --> 00:21:04.931
that's pretty rare
and very fascinating.

457
00:21:04.972 --> 00:21:08.642
Yep, huge teeth, great cook.

458
00:21:08.684 --> 00:21:11.938
Oh, and his growl has this
adorable French twang to it.

459
00:21:11.979 --> 00:21:13.940
I do love a monster
with an accent.

460
00:21:13.981 --> 00:21:15.441
I look forward to meeting him.

461
00:21:15.482 --> 00:21:17.443
Wonderful.

462
00:21:17.484 --> 00:21:21.197
If you'll excuse me,
I need to go to bed.

463
00:21:21.239 --> 00:21:23.199
- Oh.
- Yes.

464
00:21:23.241 --> 00:21:25.868
<i>♪♪</i>

465
00:21:25.910 --> 00:21:29.080
Strange girl.
[slurps]

466
00:21:29.122 --> 00:21:32.875
<i>♪♪</i>

467
00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:35.669
[both screaming]

468
00:21:35.711 --> 00:21:37.213
Hello, bathroom!

469
00:21:37.255 --> 00:21:39.423
- Sorry!
- [toilet flushing]

470
00:21:39.465 --> 00:21:42.176
Deep breaths.
You're a monster.

471
00:21:42.218 --> 00:21:43.886
You're...

472
00:21:43.928 --> 00:21:46.264
- Knock much?
- I'm sorry.

473
00:21:46.305 --> 00:21:48.933
<i>♪♪</i>

474
00:21:51.435 --> 00:21:54.230
[heart pounding]

475
00:21:56.774 --> 00:21:59.277
What is happening to me?

476
00:21:59.318 --> 00:22:02.404
Yeah, I used to work on
Maul Street, private eek-quity.

477
00:22:02.446 --> 00:22:04.531
It's good money,
but just wasn't for me.

478
00:22:04.573 --> 00:22:06.366
I wanted to give back, you know,

479
00:22:06.408 --> 00:22:08.494
so I quit, and I came here.

480
00:22:08.535 --> 00:22:14.583
<i>♪♪</i>

481
00:22:16.127 --> 00:22:18.171
[squelching]

482
00:22:18.212 --> 00:22:21.048
[low rumbling]

483
00:22:29.098 --> 00:22:30.599
[school bell ringing]

484
00:22:30.641 --> 00:22:34.979
[light music]

485
00:22:35.021 --> 00:22:36.981
- Hey, dude!
- Broski?

486
00:22:37.023 --> 00:22:39.608
<i>♪♪</i>

487
00:22:39.650 --> 00:22:41.235
Hi, Frankie.

488
00:22:41.277 --> 00:22:43.487
Oh, hey, roomie.
I got a phone.

489
00:22:43.529 --> 00:22:45.031
It'll help me build
a healthy social network,

490
00:22:45.072 --> 00:22:46.364
which is essential

491
00:22:46.406 --> 00:22:48.034
to a successful
high school experience

492
00:22:48.075 --> 00:22:49.827
according to several
hundred articles I just read.

493
00:22:49.869 --> 00:22:51.329
[Heath]
Yeah, go long, Abbey!

494
00:22:51.369 --> 00:22:53.497
Yeah, heads up!

495
00:22:53.539 --> 00:22:54.999
All right, sweet catch.

496
00:22:55.041 --> 00:22:57.417
Yes, I love football!

497
00:22:57.459 --> 00:22:59.170
Do we eat this now?

498
00:22:59.295 --> 00:23:02.298
After the game, Abbey.
We eat the foot after the game.

499
00:23:03.299 --> 00:23:05.968
- Oh, good that's not my foot.
- All right!

500
00:23:06.719 --> 00:23:09.680
Um, listen, in that
amazing brain of yours.

501
00:23:09.972 --> 00:23:12.432
Have you ever heard of
