- [woman over PA] <i>Attention, all students.</i>

1229
00:55:15.229 --> 00:55:18.732
<i>Monster biology is canceled
until further notice.</i>

1230
00:55:18.774 --> 00:55:23.279
<i>Please return all stolen limbs
to the biology department,</i>

1231
00:55:23.319 --> 00:55:25.823
<i>and if you've eaten the limb
and cannot return it,</i>

1232
00:55:25.864 --> 00:55:28.993
<i>please digest it
and disregard this message.</i>

1233
00:55:29.034 --> 00:55:30.995
Okay, let's see.

1234
00:55:31.036 --> 00:55:33.956
Just one more ingredient
left to find, and it's a doozy.

1235
00:55:33.998 --> 00:55:35.373
Snake venom.

1236
00:55:35.415 --> 00:55:36.959
The only native snake species

1237
00:55:37.001 --> 00:55:38.710
to Monster High's ecosystem
is a giant swamp viper,

1238
00:55:38.752 --> 00:55:40.296
but they're 40 feet long

1239
00:55:40.336 --> 00:55:42.338
and tend to bite your head off
if you get too close,

1240
00:55:42.380 --> 00:55:45.509
but I could probably get
another head, so I'm game.

1241
00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:49.888
No, I know where
we can find some.

1242
00:55:49.930 --> 00:55:52.683
It's just not gonna be easy.

1243
00:55:52.724 --> 00:55:54.518
<i>♪ Here I am ♪</i>

1244
00:55:55.686 --> 00:55:59.064
<i>♪♪ Pretty sure this is better
Than sunlight ♪</i>

1245
00:55:59.106 --> 00:56:02.526
<i>♪ What's the opposite
Of panic attack? ♪</i>

1246
00:56:02.567 --> 00:56:04.987
- Hi.
- Hi.

1247
00:56:05.029 --> 00:56:07.156
You gonna run away again?

1248
00:56:07.198 --> 00:56:10.909
Not this time, hopefully.
[chuckles]

1249
00:56:10.951 --> 00:56:13.704
I was wondering since
you have the inside scoop

1250
00:56:13.745 --> 00:56:15.706
on these Founders'
dinner speeches,

1251
00:56:15.747 --> 00:56:18.250
maybe I'd take you up
on that offer to work on mine?

1252
00:56:19.668 --> 00:56:21.128
Deal.

1253
00:56:21.170 --> 00:56:25.465
[creature growling]

1254
00:56:25.507 --> 00:56:27.718
- [Clawdeen] Cool spot.
- [Deuce] Right?

1255
00:56:27.759 --> 00:56:29.345
There's no cell signal,

1256
00:56:29.385 --> 00:56:30.595
so nobody comes up here anymore.

1257
00:56:30.637 --> 00:56:32.097
It's peaceful.

1258
00:56:32.139 --> 00:56:34.558
So you come here
to gather your thoughts?

1259
00:56:34.599 --> 00:56:37.061
- Yeah, I do.
- [both chuckle]

1260
00:56:37.102 --> 00:56:41.148
Monster High can definitely be
a little intense at times.

1261
00:56:41.190 --> 00:56:43.483
Your mom was a big deal
here, right?

1262
00:56:43.525 --> 00:56:45.777
Uh, yeah.

1263
00:56:45.819 --> 00:56:48.655
See, I'm the first one
in my family

1264
00:56:48.697 --> 00:56:50.406
to ever go to Monster High.

1265
00:56:50.448 --> 00:56:52.368
Gorgons aren't exactly
the most beloved of monsters.

1266
00:56:52.408 --> 00:56:54.203
Maybe it's
the deadly snake hair.

1267
00:56:54.245 --> 00:56:55.954
Are people that shallow?

1268
00:56:55.996 --> 00:56:57.581
- Yes.
- [both laugh]

1269
00:56:57.622 --> 00:56:59.041
Yeah, they are.

1270
00:56:59.875 --> 00:57:03.045
So are they
really super poisonous?

1271
00:57:03.087 --> 00:57:04.588
Think I could see them
for a sec?

1272
00:57:04.629 --> 00:57:07.258
Not a great idea.

1273
00:57:07.299 --> 00:57:08.967
You know, that's the thing.

1274
00:57:09.009 --> 00:57:11.720
You know, deadly hair,
deadly eyes.

1275
00:57:11.762 --> 00:57:14.306
Everyone makes assumptions
about me, you know?

1276
00:57:14.348 --> 00:57:16.433
I get it. Believe me.

1277
00:57:16.474 --> 00:57:18.643
In the last few years,
I was headed down a dark path

1278
00:57:18.685 --> 00:57:20.437
so I changed things up.

1279
00:57:20.478 --> 00:57:22.314
It's like I know
what I don't wanna be.

1280
00:57:22.356 --> 00:57:24.108
Now, I just gotta figure out
who I am.

1281
00:57:24.149 --> 00:57:27.611
A guy like you,
you can be anything.

1282
00:57:27.652 --> 00:57:29.154
Heck, you could run
for student council.

1283
00:57:29.196 --> 00:57:31.240
Well, who'd ever vote
for a gorgon?

1284
00:57:31.282 --> 00:57:34.285
Well, me.
You can totally do it.

1285
00:57:34.326 --> 00:57:37.037
"Vote for the candidate
with killer hair."

1286
00:57:37.079 --> 00:57:39.123
It has bite.

1287
00:57:39.164 --> 00:57:41.250
If you want it, go for it.

1288
00:57:41.292 --> 00:57:43.543
Just believe in who
you really are,

1289
00:57:43.585 --> 00:57:45.129
not who people expect you to be.

1290
00:57:45.170 --> 00:57:46.922
[upbeat music]

1291
00:57:46.964 --> 00:57:48.299
Easier said than done.

1292
00:57:49.549 --> 00:57:54.596
<i>♪ Asking for a friend
Who's got some insecurities ♪</i>

1293
00:57:54.638 --> 00:57:59.559
<i>♪ Acts like he's so confident
But it's just make-believe ♪</i>

1294
00:57:59.601 --> 00:58:02.896
<i>♪ Wanting to be myself
But, no, it ain't easy for me ♪</i>

1295
00:58:02.938 --> 00:58:04.898
- You mean your friend.
- Right.

1296
00:58:04.940 --> 00:58:08.777
<i>♪ He wants to feel less
Like he's some kind of freak ♪</i>

1297
00:58:08.819 --> 00:58:12.323
<i>♪ Ay-yi-yi
Something about when I look ♪</i>

1298
00:58:12.364 --> 00:58:14.616
<i>♪ In your eye-eye-eyes ♪</i>

1299
00:58:14.658 --> 00:58:15.867
- You?
- Yeah.

1300
00:58:16.493 --> 00:58:19.121
<i>♪ Makes me feel like
I can be my real self ♪</i>

1301
00:58:19.163 --> 00:58:23.708
<i>♪ Oh, I'm so sick of trying
To be somebody else ♪</i>

1302
00:58:23.750 --> 00:58:27.212
<i>♪ Can I tell the truth
Feel like I can trust you ♪</i>

1303
00:58:27.254 --> 00:58:29.423
Now, imagine never taking
these glasses off.

1304
00:58:29.465 --> 00:58:31.842
No one trusts me.
Teachers think I'm sleeping.

1305
00:58:31.883 --> 00:58:33.969
- Could I see you without them?
- Ooh, dangerous.

1306
00:58:34.011 --> 00:58:35.804
I just wanna see the real you.

1307
00:58:35.846 --> 00:58:38.140
<i>♪ Had a lot of fake friends
In my life ♪</i>

1308
00:58:38.182 --> 00:58:40.767
<i>- ♪ Who never had my back ♪</i>
- Oh, yeah?

1309
00:58:40.809 --> 00:58:42.394
<i>♪ But I can tell
That ain't you ♪</i>

1310
00:58:42.811 --> 00:58:45.397
<i>♪ Who would ever, who would
Ever do a thing like that?</i>

1311
00:58:45.439 --> 00:58:47.983
<i>♪ Ooh ♪</i>

1312
00:58:48.025 --> 00:58:50.944
<i>♪ Feel like
I can count on you ♪</i>

1313
00:58:50.986 --> 00:58:53.905
<i>♪ Yeah, I feel
The same way, too ♪</i>

1314
00:58:53.947 --> 00:58:58.576
<i>♪ Ay-yi-yi
Something about when I look ♪</i>

1315
00:58:58.618 --> 00:59:01.455
<i>♪ In your eye-eye-eyes ♪</i>

1316
00:59:01.497 --> 00:59:04.958
<i>♪ Makes me feel like
I can be my real self ♪</i>

1317
00:59:05.000 --> 00:59:10.005
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, I'm so sick
Of trying to be somebody else ♪</i>

1318
00:59:10.047 --> 00:59:13.467
<i>♪ Can I tell the truth
Feel like I can trust you ♪</i>

1319
00:59:13.509 --> 00:59:15.511
So how's the real me?

1320
00:59:15.552 --> 00:59:17.054
It must be so hard

1321
00:59:17.095 --> 00:59:19.181
never being able to stare
into somebody's eyes.

1322
00:59:19.223 --> 00:59:21.392
Especially a wolf like you.

1323
00:59:21.433 --> 00:59:24.395
[both] <i>♪ Ay-yi-yi ♪</i>

1324
00:59:24.436 --> 00:59:29.024
<i>♪ Something about when I look
In your eye-eye-eyes ♪</i>

1325
00:59:29.066 --> 00:59:32.861
<i>♪ Makes me feel like
I can be my real self ♪</i>

1326
00:59:32.903 --> 00:59:37.574
<i>♪ Oh, oh, oh, I'm so sick
Of trying to be somebody else ♪</i>

1327
00:59:37.615 --> 00:59:41.370
<i>♪ Can I tell you the truth
Feel like I can trust you ♪</i>

1328
00:59:45.457 --> 00:59:48.001
I have to admit something.

1329
00:59:48.793 --> 00:59:52.005
I didn't just wanna work
on my speech and hang out.

1330
00:59:52.047 --> 00:59:57.177
I did, I did, but there's also
something else I need.

1331
00:59:57.219 --> 00:59:59.054
What?

1332
00:59:59.930 --> 01:00:01.265
Snake venom.

1333
01:00:02.140 --> 01:00:05.060
I can't really talk about it,
but it's important.

1334
01:00:05.561 --> 01:00:07.354
Snake venom from my snakes?

1335
01:00:07.979 --> 01:00:09.773
Yeah.

1336
01:00:09.814 --> 01:00:11.567
Well, why didn't you
just say so?

1337
01:00:11.649 --> 01:00:14.861
Sure.
All you had to do is ask.

1338
01:00:14.903 --> 01:00:17.281
Okay, the trick is not
to look them in the eye.

1339
01:00:17.322 --> 01:00:19.533
- They're a little feisty.
- Really? Oh.

1340
01:00:19.575 --> 01:00:21.701
Yep.
All right, guys, be nice.

1341
01:00:21.743 --> 01:00:24.580
- She's a friend.
- [snakes rattling, hissing]

1342
01:00:24.621 --> 01:00:27.416
Hi. [laughs]

1343
01:00:27.458 --> 01:00:29.876
[Draculaura]
He has a snake named Mo?

1344
01:00:29.918 --> 01:00:33.671
Yeah, and let me tell you,
you don't wanna mess with Mo.

1345
01:00:33.713 --> 01:00:35.257
So he just gave you the venom?

1346
01:00:35.299 --> 01:00:37.217
- Yeah.
- It was that easy?

1347
01:00:37.259 --> 01:00:40.095
- Yes, we're friends.
- He is so into you.

1348
01:00:40.137 --> 01:00:43.056
- What?
- Totally into you.

1349
01:00:43.098 --> 01:00:44.682
No.

1350
01:00:44.724 --> 01:00:46.726
Definitely into you.

1351
01:00:46.768 --> 01:00:50.230
- Really?
- Yes.

1352
01:00:50.272 --> 01:00:51.689
Now let's open that door.

1353
01:00:51.731 --> 01:00:54.234
[groans]

1354
01:00:55.527 --> 01:00:57.446
Okay, mace wing.

1355
01:00:57.488 --> 01:01:00.157
Now the ogre bone.
Mm, just a pinch.

1356
01:01:01.158 --> 01:01:03.660
And now it just says,
"Mix ingredients well."

1357
01:01:03.701 --> 01:01:07.038
<i>♪♪</i>

1358
01:01:07.080 --> 01:01:09.082
Okay, let's hope this works.

1359
01:01:10.875 --> 01:01:12.336
Bring the power to my fist,

1360
01:01:12.377 --> 01:01:14.630
release the hold
with gathered mist.

1361
01:01:14.671 --> 01:01:20.135
<i>♪♪</i>

1362
01:01:23.430 --> 01:01:25.307
Try again.

1363
01:01:25.349 --> 01:01:27.976
<i>♪♪</i>

1364
01:01:28.018 --> 01:01:29.645
Bring the power to my fist,

1365
01:01:29.686 --> 01:01:31.688
release the hold
with gathered mist.

1366
01:01:31.729 --> 01:01:37.569
<i>♪♪</i>

1367
01:01:42.282 --> 01:01:45.202
I guess I'm just
not good enough.

1368
01:01:45.243 --> 01:01:46.911
Oh.

1369
01:01:46.953 --> 01:01:51.500
- So we try again tomorrow.
- Right, right.

1370
01:01:51.542 --> 01:01:57.589
<i>♪♪</i>

1371
01:01:58.507 --> 01:02:02.719
Well, well,
what do we have here?

1372
01:02:02.760 --> 01:02:04.804
Oh, sparks.

1373
01:02:04.846 --> 01:02:06.306
What's the punishment

1374
01:02:06.348 --> 01:02:08.725
for students
out after curfew, Mr. Komos?

1375
01:02:08.766 --> 01:02:11.353
Per ghoul code,
one month detention.

1376
01:02:11.395 --> 01:02:13.230
That's right.

1377
01:02:13.271 --> 01:02:16.692
But we have a much more serious
problem, don't we, students?

1378
01:02:16.774 --> 01:02:18.569
The fundamental values
of Monster High

1379
01:02:18.610 --> 01:02:19.986
have been betrayed.

1380
01:02:20.028 --> 01:02:22.406
Our unnatural order
has been offended.

1381
01:02:22.447 --> 01:02:24.782
Headmistress, I can explain...

1382
01:02:24.824 --> 01:02:26.993
Witchcraft.

1383
01:02:27.035 --> 01:02:29.496
Wait, what?

1384
01:02:29.538 --> 01:02:32.123
It has been reported
that you, Draculaura,

1385
01:02:32.165 --> 01:02:34.501
have been practicing witchcraft.

1386
01:02:34.543 --> 01:02:36.961
In my mortal life,
I studied with Heka,

1387
01:02:37.003 --> 01:02:38.755
god of magic and medicine.

1388
01:02:38.796 --> 01:02:42.300
I know an incantation
when one's thrown at me.

1389
01:02:42.342 --> 01:02:44.595
Thank you, Cleo.

1390
01:02:46.304 --> 01:02:48.557
Open your bag, please.

1391
01:02:50.100 --> 01:02:51.560
[sighs]

1392
01:02:51.602 --> 01:02:54.229
[tense music]

1393
01:02:54.271 --> 01:02:57.315
Witchcraft will not
be tolerated at Monster High.

1394
01:02:57.357 --> 01:02:59.276
I'm so sorry.
I'll never do it again.

1395
01:02:59.317 --> 01:03:01.695
- What will your father think?
- Please, you can't tell him.

1396
01:03:01.737 --> 01:03:05.699
You've left me no choice.
And you two, encouraging her.

1397
01:03:05.741 --> 01:03:07.367
You should be ashamed

1398
01:03:07.409 --> 01:03:09.369
for not living up to
the standards expected of you.

1399
01:03:09.411 --> 01:03:13.498
[growling and shrieking]

1400
01:03:13.540 --> 01:03:15.417
What is that?

1401
01:03:15.459 --> 01:03:17.043
It's like the school
is screaming!

1402
01:03:17.085 --> 01:03:18.629
<i>♪♪</i>

1403
01:03:18.670 --> 01:03:20.213
- Oh!
- Look out!

1404
01:03:20.255 --> 01:03:22.840
[screams]

1405
01:03:25.761 --> 01:03:28.930
Is everyone all right?
Is anyone hurt?

1406
01:03:28.972 --> 01:03:30.932
I'm all right.

1407
01:03:31.266 --> 01:03:34.102
[panting]

1408
01:03:34.144 --> 01:03:37.188
You saved me.

1409
01:03:37.230 --> 01:03:39.524
- You're welcome.
- [Bloodgood] Go to your rooms now.

1410
01:03:39.566 --> 01:03:42.110
Use the south stairs.

1411
01:03:42.152 --> 01:03:44.362
I didn't wanna believe
that this could happen again,

1412
01:03:44.404 --> 01:03:48.659
but these signs, it's
the school itself crying out,

1413
01:03:48.700 --> 01:03:51.244
and it can only mean one thing.

1414
01:03:51.286 --> 01:03:53.413
There's an untrue monster heart
among us.

1415
01:03:53.455 --> 01:03:55.123
- A human?
- Yes.

1416
01:03:55.165 --> 01:03:56.667
And if we don't find out
who it is

1417
01:03:56.708 --> 01:03:58.627
and get rid of the threat,

1418
01:03:58.669 --> 01:04:00.295
the school
could tear itself apart.

1419
01:04:01.797 --> 01:04:04.132
The Founders' Day dinner
is tomorrow.

1420
01:04:04.174 --> 01:04:05.467
Do we postpone?

1421
01:04:05.509 --> 01:04:06.884
[Bloodgood]
It's such an important event.

1422
01:04:06.926 --> 01:04:10.096
The donors that keep
this school open.

1423
01:04:11.389 --> 01:04:13.099
Keep the dinner, Headmistress.

1424
01:04:13.141 --> 01:04:14.934
I'll help find the human.

1425
01:04:14.976 --> 01:04:20.982
<i>♪♪</i>

1426
01:04:21.024 --> 01:04:23.067
Bloodgood really is terrifying.

1427
01:04:23.109 --> 01:04:26.446
Draculaura, I'm sorry.
It's me.

1428
01:04:26.488 --> 01:04:28.114
I'm the one
destroying the school.

1429
01:04:28.156 --> 01:04:30.367
I'm putting everyone in danger.

1430
01:04:30.408 --> 01:04:32.869
I'm sorry for all of it.

1431
01:04:35.747 --> 01:04:37.957
She'll be okay.

1432
01:04:39.459 --> 01:04:43.129
[somber music]

1433
01:04:43.171 --> 01:04:46.800
[howling in distance]

1434
01:04:46.842 --> 01:04:52.514
<i>♪♪</i>

1435
01:04:55.933 --> 01:05:01.356
<i>♪ Here I am
I'm coming out of the dark ♪</i>

1436
01:05:01.398 --> 01:05:03.483
<i>♪♪</i>

1437
01:05:03.525 --> 01:05:05.985
<i>♪ Was it all a mistake ♪</i>

1438
01:05:06.027 --> 01:05:10.198
<i>♪ To show my beating heart? ♪</i>

1439
01:05:10.240 --> 01:05:12.116
Goodbye.

1440
01:05:12.158 --> 01:05:15.704
<i>♪ Is there nowhere
I can be free? ♪</i>

1441
01:05:15.746 --> 01:05:19.708
<i>♪ Is there no place
I'm meant to be? ♪</i>

1442
01:05:19.750 --> 01:05:25.672
<i>♪ Here I am, I'm crawling
Back into the dark ♪</i>

1443
01:05:25.714 --> 01:05:28.925
<i>♪ Back into the dark ♪</i>

1444
01:05:28.966 --> 01:05:33.012
<i>♪♪</i>

1445
01:05:36.892 --> 01:05:41.145
[soft music]

1446
01:05:41.605 --> 01:05:43.064
[wings flapping]

1447
01:05:45.400 --> 01:05:47.151
Ow, sunlight.

1448
01:05:47.193 --> 01:05:50.530
- Not my favorite.
- What are you doing here?

1449
01:05:50.572 --> 01:05:52.741
Nice, you get me busted,

1450
01:05:52.783 --> 01:05:55.368
and you're the one
with the attitude.

1451
01:05:55.410 --> 01:05:57.704
<i>♪♪</i>

1452
01:05:57.746 --> 01:05:59.163
I'm sorry about your dad.

1453
01:06:00.916 --> 01:06:04.419
He'll forgive me someday.
I have eternity on my side.

1454
01:06:04.461 --> 01:06:07.714
<i>♪♪</i>

1455
01:06:07.756 --> 01:06:11.008
I think we've almost
caught up to her.

1456
01:06:11.050 --> 01:06:13.136
Oh, hi.

1457
01:06:14.512 --> 01:06:16.055
How did you find me?

1458
01:06:16.973 --> 01:06:19.267
You didn't turn off your
"Find my Fiends App."

1459
01:06:19.309 --> 01:06:21.185
It's alarmingly accurate.

1460
01:06:21.227 --> 01:06:24.564
That's right.
We're friends, remember?

1461
01:06:24.606 --> 01:06:27.108
We're not letting you run away
when you need us the most.

1462
01:06:27.150 --> 01:06:29.026
- [heartbeat pounding]
- If I go back,

1463
01:06:29.068 --> 01:06:31.237
I just put everyone in danger.

1464
01:06:31.279 --> 01:06:32.572
Let's face it.

1465
01:06:32.614 --> 01:06:35.659
I'm not monster enough
for Monster High.

1466
01:06:35.700 --> 01:06:38.119
[heart beating faster]

1467
01:06:38.161 --> 01:06:39.746
Look at me.

1468
01:06:39.788 --> 01:06:42.874
I don't belong there.
I don't belong anywhere.

1469
01:06:42.916 --> 01:06:44.292
You belong with us, Clawdeen.

1470
01:06:44.334 --> 01:06:48.338
But I don't know
how to stay with you!

1471
01:06:48.379 --> 01:06:50.715
- [grunts]
- [both] Clawdeen!

1472
01:06:50.757 --> 01:06:53.593
<i>♪♪</i>

1473
01:06:53.635 --> 01:06:56.721
Wait, is that...

1474
01:06:56.763 --> 01:06:59.933
- It looks like...
- It sure does.

1475
01:06:59.975 --> 01:07:02.435
- So you think?
- I don't know.

1476
01:07:02.477 --> 01:07:05.062
It's worth a shot, right?

1477
01:07:05.104 --> 01:07:07.231
♪♪

1478
01:07:07.273 --> 01:07:08.859
[gate creaking]

1479
01:07:08.900 --> 01:07:12.069
♪♪

1480
01:07:14.071 --> 01:07:16.115
Clawdeen!

1481
01:07:17.074 --> 01:07:19.118
[Bloodgood] Look at you.
You are so handsome.

1482
01:07:19.160 --> 01:07:21.913
The Founders' Dinner.
I totally forgot.

1483
01:07:21.955 --> 01:07:23.581
My dad's coming.

1484
01:07:23.623 --> 01:07:25.583
Aren't you supposed
to give a speech?

1485
01:07:25.625 --> 01:07:28.545
Yes, to honor my mother.

1486
01:07:28.586 --> 01:07:30.421
Let's just get this done.

1487
01:07:31.548 --> 01:07:34.926
Madam, silver is your color.
Drinks inside.

1488
01:07:34.968 --> 01:07:37.387
Enjoy your evening.

1489
01:07:37.428 --> 01:07:39.096
Any trace of the human?

1490
01:07:39.138 --> 01:07:41.558
No, not yet.

1491
01:07:41.599 --> 01:07:45.186
Hello, welcome back.
So wonderful to see you again.

1492
01:07:45.228 --> 01:07:46.771
<i>♪♪</i>

1493
01:07:46.813 --> 01:07:48.356
Now, what?

1494
01:07:48.398 --> 01:07:49.774
Do we need to freak you out
so you turn human?

1495
01:07:49.816 --> 01:07:51.401
- Pretend I'm Deuce.
- What?

1496
01:07:51.442 --> 01:07:54.111
No, I think I've got this now.

1497
01:07:54.153 --> 01:07:59.158
[heartbeat pounding]

1498
01:07:59.200 --> 01:08:01.912
It's like you have a superpower

1499
01:08:01.953 --> 01:08:04.622
that makes you less powerful.

1500
01:08:05.707 --> 01:08:08.125
Hopefully not for long.

1501
01:08:08.167 --> 01:08:12.589
<i>♪♪</i>

1502
01:08:12.630 --> 01:08:15.008
[clanking]

1503
01:08:15.050 --> 01:08:18.177
<i>♪♪</i>

1504
01:08:18.219 --> 01:08:21.431
[chuckles]
Holy headless horsewoman!

1505
01:08:21.472 --> 01:08:24.308
- It worked!
- It just needed a human hand.

1506
01:08:24.350 --> 01:08:27.270
Hyde's secret half.

1507
01:08:27.311 --> 01:08:29.439
Let's do this.

1508
01:08:29.480 --> 01:08:35.612
<i>♪♪</i>

1509
01:08:36.279 --> 01:08:38.573
What is this?

1510
01:08:38.615 --> 01:08:41.451
It's just a tomb.

1511
01:08:41.492 --> 01:08:44.037
[Frankie] An ogre's tomb,
from the looks of it.

1512
01:08:44.079 --> 01:08:46.748
Hey, it's Agmon the terrible.

1513
01:08:46.790 --> 01:08:49.751
No. No, no,
Hyde's lab is here.

1514
01:08:49.793 --> 01:08:51.086
It has to be.

1515
01:08:51.127 --> 01:08:52.670
He locked that door
to protect it.

1516
01:08:52.712 --> 01:08:54.297
There's gotta be another door.

1517
01:08:54.338 --> 01:08:56.382
<i>♪♪</i>

1518
01:08:56.424 --> 01:08:58.093
Hey, look at this.

1519
01:08:58.134 --> 01:09:01.721
Under the monocle,
it's Hyde's code.

1520
01:09:01.763 --> 01:09:04.557
- What does it say?
- It says "push."

1521
01:09:04.599 --> 01:09:06.643
- It's a button!
- It's an eye.

1522
01:09:06.684 --> 01:09:08.103
- It's a button.
- It's an eye.

1523
01:09:08.144 --> 01:09:10.396
It's a button. Try it.

1524
01:09:10.438 --> 01:09:12.356
- [eyeball squishes]
- It's an eye.

1525
01:09:12.398 --> 01:09:14.275
[rumbling]

1526
01:09:14.317 --> 01:09:16.778
<i>♪♪</i>

1527
01:09:16.820 --> 01:09:18.195
And a button.

1528
01:09:18.237 --> 01:09:19.990
We're both right.

1529
01:09:21.866 --> 01:09:23.868
Great.

1530
01:09:23.910 --> 01:09:30.166
<i>♪♪</i>

1531
01:09:33.294 --> 01:09:35.046
We did it.

1532
01:09:36.131 --> 01:09:41.136
<i>♪♪</i>

1533
01:09:49.602 --> 01:09:51.437
There's a switch.

1534
01:09:52.313 --> 01:09:53.898
<i>♪♪</i>

1535
01:09:53.940 --> 01:09:55.525
[electricity zapping]

1536
01:09:55.566 --> 01:09:59.403
[machinery whirring]

1537
01:09:59.445 --> 01:10:01.114
Wow.

1538
01:10:01.156 --> 01:10:07.453
<i>♪♪</i>

1539
01:10:09.497 --> 01:10:11.666
Hyde kept busy.

1540
01:10:11.708 --> 01:10:14.335
Is that calcium chloride?

1541
01:10:14.377 --> 01:10:16.129
Ammonium nitrate?

1542
01:10:16.171 --> 01:10:19.966
Oh, is this plutonium?

1543
01:10:20.008 --> 01:10:23.970
Oh, have I died again and gone
to mad scientist monster heaven?

1544
01:10:24.012 --> 01:10:26.139
Stay on mission, Frankie.

1545
01:10:26.181 --> 01:10:28.933
Can I just make one teensy
inteensy little explosion first?

1546
01:10:28.975 --> 01:10:34.271
<i>♪♪</i>

1547
01:10:34.313 --> 01:10:36.107
Hyde's code.

1548
01:10:36.149 --> 01:10:37.817
It's his formula.

1549
01:10:37.859 --> 01:10:39.736
No more human.

1550
01:10:39.777 --> 01:10:42.321
<i>♪♪</i>

1551
01:10:42.363 --> 01:10:45.116
I'm free.

1552
01:10:45.158 --> 01:10:47.535
[Dad]
<i>Remember, the school</i>

1553
01:10:47.577 --> 01:10:49.412
<i>is serious
about keeping humans out.</i>

1554
01:10:49.453 --> 01:10:54.375
<i>♪♪</i>

1555
01:11:03.676 --> 01:11:05.636
We found it.

1556
01:11:05.678 --> 01:11:07.764
That's fantastic!

1557
01:11:07.805 --> 01:11:09.140
High five!

1558
01:11:10.600 --> 01:11:13.352
What's wrong?

1559
01:11:13.394 --> 01:11:16.397
If I drink this...

1560
01:11:16.439 --> 01:11:17.941
it's like I'm erasing him.

1561
01:11:17.982 --> 01:11:20.651
Erasing who?

1562
01:11:20.693 --> 01:11:22.403
My dad.

1563
01:11:22.445 --> 01:11:25.240
My secret half is him.

1564
01:11:25.281 --> 01:11:29.827
Do I really wanna
just give up who I am?

1565
01:11:30.578 --> 01:11:31.621
- No, you don't.
- [all gasp]

1566
01:11:31.662 --> 01:11:32.956
What?

1567
01:11:32.997 --> 01:11:34.373
- No...
- Mr. Komos, we can explain.

1568
01:11:34.415 --> 01:11:35.917
There's no need to explain,
Frankie.

1569
01:11:35.959 --> 01:11:37.710
I was worried
this was your plan.

1570
01:11:37.752 --> 01:11:39.503
Clawdeen,
do not take that potion.

1571
01:11:39.545 --> 01:11:41.047
Trust me.

1572
01:11:41.089 --> 01:11:44.008
I know what it's like
to feel like an outsider,

1573
01:11:44.050 --> 01:11:46.302
to have to keep secrets.

1574
01:11:46.343 --> 01:11:48.345
<i>♪♪</i>

1575
01:11:48.387 --> 01:11:51.348
I'm part human, too.

1576
01:11:51.390 --> 01:11:52.725
- What?
- Really?

1577
01:11:52.767 --> 01:11:55.853
Yes, and giving up who you are,

1578
01:11:55.895 --> 01:11:57.480
this isn't the answer.

1579
01:11:57.521 --> 01:11:59.690
<i>♪♪</i>

1580
01:11:59.732 --> 01:12:01.692
I know a better way.

1581
01:12:01.734 --> 01:12:07.531
<i>♪♪</i>

1582
01:12:15.372 --> 01:12:17.541
Thank you.

1583
01:12:19.085 --> 01:12:20.170
[all] No!

1584
01:12:20.211 --> 01:12:22.379
- No!
- What are you doing?

1585
01:12:22.421 --> 01:12:25.633
[grunts]

1586
01:12:25.675 --> 01:12:27.969
I haven't been
entirely forthcoming with you.

1587
01:12:28.011 --> 01:12:30.763
- [retches]
- Mr. Komos?

1588
01:12:30.805 --> 01:12:32.515
Nope.

1589
01:12:32.556 --> 01:12:35.018
Komos was
my mother's maiden name.

1590
01:12:36.393 --> 01:12:38.395
My name is Hyde.

1591
01:12:38.437 --> 01:12:40.439
Hyde Junior, technically.

1592
01:12:40.481 --> 01:12:43.026
I was named after my father.
[grunts]

1593
01:12:43.067 --> 01:12:45.153
You're Hyde's son?

1594
01:12:45.195 --> 01:12:48.114
That's what I just said.
Try to keep up, Clawdeen.

1595
01:12:48.156 --> 01:12:51.075
You listen so well in class.

1596
01:12:51.117 --> 01:12:52.910
I have been looking

1597
01:12:52.952 --> 01:12:55.872
for this place
ever since I arrived this year.

1598
01:12:55.913 --> 01:12:58.374
I found the lab journals,
of course.

1599
01:12:58.415 --> 01:13:01.169
Cracking that code...
[laughs]

1600
01:13:01.211 --> 01:13:04.964
I've got to admit,
I was stumped. Whew!

1601
01:13:05.006 --> 01:13:07.342
That was pretty genius
there, Frankie.

1602
01:13:07.383 --> 01:13:10.553
[groaning]

1603
01:13:10.594 --> 01:13:13.097
[dramatic music]

1604
01:13:13.139 --> 01:13:15.683
And opening
that door was clever.

1605
01:13:15.725 --> 01:13:17.560
Dad didn't pass down
his alter ego.

1606
01:13:17.601 --> 01:13:22.232
So without a true human hand,
I was never gonna open it.

1607
01:13:22.273 --> 01:13:25.860
Clawdeen, you get an A+.

1608
01:13:25.902 --> 01:13:28.571
So you just wanted
to turn a monster, too?

1609
01:13:28.612 --> 01:13:30.865
So you could stay
at Monster High?

1610
01:13:30.907 --> 01:13:33.743
[laughs] Oh, I don't wanna
stay at Monster High.

1611
01:13:33.784 --> 01:13:35.870
[grunts]

1612
01:13:35.912 --> 01:13:38.789
I'm going
to destroy Monster High.

1613
01:13:38.831 --> 01:13:43.086
[screaming]

1614
01:13:43.127 --> 01:13:46.714
- [yelping]
- [clothes ripping]

1615
01:13:46.756 --> 01:13:52.553
<i>♪♪</i>

1616
01:13:54.972 --> 01:13:57.975
[laughs] Ohh.

1617
01:14:00.937 --> 01:14:04.648
See, this potion doesn't
just turn you into a monster.

1618
01:14:04.690 --> 01:14:08.778
It turns you
into the ultimate monster.

1619
01:14:08.819 --> 01:14:11.948
My dad was a smart man.

1620
01:14:11.989 --> 01:14:13.741
His formula was
gonna be his revenge

1621
01:14:13.783 --> 01:14:16.369
against all those monsters
that ruined his life.

1622
01:14:16.411 --> 01:14:17.995
Though, of course,
he was expelled

1623
01:14:18.037 --> 01:14:19.580
before he could take it,

1624
01:14:19.622 --> 01:14:23.126
so I'm here to finish the job.

1625
01:14:23.167 --> 01:14:24.543
Ahh!

1626
01:14:24.585 --> 01:14:26.087
Draculaura!

1627
01:14:27.713 --> 01:14:29.673
[laughs]

1628
01:14:29.715 --> 01:14:32.343
[bat screeching]

1629
01:14:33.719 --> 01:14:36.055
[laughs]

1630
01:14:36.097 --> 01:14:38.099
- Neat!
- What have you done to her?

1631
01:14:38.141 --> 01:14:39.600
I've stolen her powers.

1632
01:14:39.642 --> 01:14:41.811
Her very monster essence.

1633
01:14:41.852 --> 01:14:44.480
It's perfect.

1634
01:14:45.398 --> 01:14:48.943
And tonight is
the perfect night.

1635
01:14:48.985 --> 01:14:51.570
They're all here...
Bloodgood

1636
01:14:51.612 --> 01:14:54.531
and all the school's
most prestigious officers.

1637
01:14:54.573 --> 01:14:57.327
Once I've brought down
Monster High,

1638
01:14:57.368 --> 01:15:00.496
I'll move on to those
that actually killed my father.

1639
01:15:00.537 --> 01:15:02.332
Humans.

1640
01:15:03.833 --> 01:15:06.002
Oh, man, I feel good!

1641
01:15:06.043 --> 01:15:08.129
Look at this rockin' bod!

1642
01:15:08.171 --> 01:15:09.588
- Quick, run!
- Ahh! Ahh!

1643
01:15:09.630 --> 01:15:12.425
- Go!
- [groaning]

1644
01:15:12.467 --> 01:15:15.345
<i>♪♪</i>

1645
01:15:15.386 --> 01:15:18.014
Hurry.

1646
01:15:18.055 --> 01:15:20.933
- He's not gonna stop.
- I'm so weak.

1647
01:15:20.975 --> 01:15:23.353
We need to get her help
and warn everyone.

1648
01:15:23.394 --> 01:15:25.896
- [Hyde Jr. screams]
- [glass shattering]

1649
01:15:25.938 --> 01:15:29.775
Wait, no! He locked the door.
We can't get out.

1650
01:15:29.817 --> 01:15:31.610
Very smart, Frankie!

1651
01:15:31.652 --> 01:15:32.945
- You can't get out.
- [pounding on door]

1652
01:15:32.987 --> 01:15:34.613
Draculaura!
No, no, no, no, no.

1653
01:15:34.655 --> 01:15:36.073
[thudding]

1654
01:15:36.115 --> 01:15:38.451
- What do we do?
- Quick, call someone.

1655
01:15:38.493 --> 01:15:39.869
- Okay.
- [Hyde Jr.] Clawdeen!

1656
01:15:39.910 --> 01:15:41.329
How?

1657
01:15:41.371 --> 01:15:43.331
You haven't used your phone
as a phone yet?

1658
01:15:43.373 --> 01:15:44.957
I just thought
it was for social media.

1659
01:15:44.999 --> 01:15:47.502
And the only friends
I have in here are you two.

1660
01:15:47.543 --> 01:15:49.795
And well... Cleo.

1661
01:15:49.837 --> 01:15:52.048
Cleo? Go live!

1662
01:15:52.089 --> 01:15:53.883
- Okay...
- [banging on door]

1663
01:15:55.009 --> 01:15:56.177
[phone chimes]

1664
01:15:56.219 --> 01:15:57.553
What's this?

1665
01:15:57.594 --> 01:15:59.180
<i>Cleo, we need your help.</i>

1666
01:15:59.222 --> 01:16:01.724
<i>Mr. Komos is
actually Hyde's son.</i>

1667
01:16:01.765 --> 01:16:03.393
<i>He's gone psycho!</i>

1668
01:16:03.434 --> 01:16:05.728
<i>He's here for revenge
to destroy Monster High.</i>

1669
01:16:05.769 --> 01:16:07.646
<i>We're trapped,
and Draculaura's hurt.</i>

1670
01:16:07.688 --> 01:16:09.023
<i>Please get help.</i>

1671
01:16:09.065 --> 01:16:11.859
<i>♪♪</i>

1672
01:16:12.318 --> 01:16:15.071
[tense music]

1673
01:16:15.112 --> 01:16:20.159
<i>♪♪</i>

1674
01:16:21.994 --> 01:16:23.538
- [slams table]
- [gasping]

1675
01:16:23.579 --> 01:16:27.291
Bloodgood, I find it
highly disrespectful...

1676
01:16:27.333 --> 01:16:29.377
- [cell phone buzzes]
- That she would be so late.

1677
01:16:29.419 --> 01:16:31.212
[Bloodgood]
I know. I'm mortified.

1678
01:16:31.254 --> 01:16:33.589
Clawdeen's been
such a conscientious student.

1679
01:16:35.258 --> 01:16:36.300
Any word from her?

1680
01:16:36.342 --> 01:16:38.594
Uh, no. I'm sorry.

1681
01:16:38.635 --> 01:16:42.723
[phone buzzing]

1682
01:16:42.765 --> 01:16:45.642
Cleo, I can't talk right now.

1683
01:16:46.394 --> 01:16:47.562
What?

1684
01:16:47.603 --> 01:16:48.979
[pounding on door]

1685
01:16:49.021 --> 01:16:51.607
That door's not gonna hold.

1686
01:16:51.648 --> 01:16:52.608
- All right!
- Gotta get out of here.

1687
01:16:52.649 --> 01:16:54.151
Enough fun and games!

1688
01:16:54.193 --> 01:16:56.195
- Hey?
- Huh?

1689
01:16:56.237 --> 01:16:57.654
I can try the spell it again.

1690
01:16:57.696 --> 01:16:59.156
The mist of releasing,
I have some left.

1691
01:16:59.198 --> 01:17:00.699
Your powers are gone.

1692
01:17:00.741 --> 01:17:03.369
My monster powers.
Witchcraft is different.

1693
01:17:03.411 --> 01:17:05.371
Help me.

1694
01:17:05.413 --> 01:17:06.789
Come on.

1695
01:17:06.830 --> 01:17:08.958
[shouting, pounding]

1696
01:17:11.043 --> 01:17:12.962
Bring the power to my fist,

1697
01:17:13.003 --> 01:17:15.756
release the hold
with gathered mist.

1698
01:17:15.798 --> 01:17:21.053
<i>♪♪</i>

1699
01:17:26.934 --> 01:17:29.145
You did it!

1700
01:17:29.186 --> 01:17:33.316
- Draculaura!
- [pounding on door]

1701
01:17:33.357 --> 01:17:36.360
Clawdeen, Clawdeen!

1702
01:17:36.402 --> 01:17:38.613
- Is she okay?
- I don't know.

1703
01:17:38.654 --> 01:17:40.573
Komos did this.
He can take our powers.

1704
01:17:40.615 --> 01:17:42.032
- What?
- Oh, my Ra!

1705
01:17:42.074 --> 01:17:43.826
- Where's Komos?
- Why is he doing this?

1706
01:17:43.867 --> 01:17:46.870
<i>♪♪</i>

1707
01:17:46.912 --> 01:17:50.666
You know, you kids are really
starting to annoy me.

1708
01:17:50.707 --> 01:17:53.503
[cracking neck]

1709
01:17:53.544 --> 01:17:56.672
- Is that Komos?
- Yes.

1710
01:17:56.713 --> 01:17:59.216
Oh, good, we have company.

1711
01:17:59.258 --> 01:18:02.178
[wind shrieking]

1712
01:18:02.219 --> 01:18:03.429
What is that?

1713
01:18:03.471 --> 01:18:06.307
[girl]
The school is alive!

1714
01:18:06.349 --> 01:18:08.225
[boy]
Ugh, and it's not happy.

1715
01:18:08.267 --> 01:18:10.144
Wow, that is loud.

1716
01:18:10.186 --> 01:18:11.854
This school is so weird.

1717
01:18:11.895 --> 01:18:14.106
I wouldn't do anything you
don't want the world to see.

1718
01:18:14.148 --> 01:18:15.816
Oh, don't you worry.

1719
01:18:15.858 --> 01:18:17.734
I'm gonna do exactly
what I want the world to see,

1720
01:18:17.776 --> 01:18:19.278
destroy this school.

1721
01:18:19.320 --> 01:18:20.779
